Description: Sherd of shoulder of pottery amphora or similar closed vase; turn of neck just preserved. Light brown micaceous clay. Graffito on shoulder
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 101 (= Well 5)
Curator's comments: marked '31' in pencil. There is a preserved the start of an turn at the edge of the fragment, indicating that we have here a jar with angled shoulder. The micaceous clay rules out an origin from Cyprus or the Levant. Possibly from a large version of the 'Samian lekythos'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.007)
